  "prompt": "Which phone is best to buy under 17000 rs?",
  "response": "As of 2023, there are several good smartphones available under \u20b917,000 in India that you can consider. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Redmi Note 10 Pro**\n   - Display: 6.67-inch Full HD+ AMOLED\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 732G\n   - RAM: 6GB/8GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB\n   - Camera: 64MP + 8MP + 5MP + 2MP | 16MP front camera\n   - Battery: 5020mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n2. **Realme 8**\n   - Display: 6.4-inch Full HD+ Super AMOLED\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G95\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB/8GB\n   - Storage: 128GB\n   - Camera: 64MP + 8MP + 2MP + 2MP | 16MP front camera\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 30W fast charging\n\n3. **Poco X3**\n   - Display: 6.67-inch Full HD+ LCD with 120Hz refresh rate\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 732G\n   - RAM: 6GB/8GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB\n   - Camera: 64MP + 13MP + 2MP + 2MP | 20MP front camera\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n4. **Samsung Galaxy M32**\n   - Display: 6.4-inch Full HD+ Super AMOLED with 90Hz refresh rate\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G80\n   - RAM: 4GB/6GB\n   - Storage: 64GB/128GB\n   - Camera: 64MP + 8MP + 2MP + 2MP | 20MP front camera\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 15W fast charging\n\n5. **Moto G60**\n   - Display: 6.78-inch Full HD+ LCD with 120Hz refresh rate\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 732G\n   - RAM: 6GB\n   - Storage: 128GB\n   - Camera: 108MP + 8MP + 2MP | 32MP front camera\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 20W TurboPower charging\n\nThese models offer a good balance of performance, display quality, camera capabilities, and battery life. The best choice depends on your specific needs and preferences, such as camera quality, gaming performance, battery longevity, design, and user interface.",
